parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The radiator support mount rot can cause the A/C condenser to fall through and compromise the body mounts, leading to potential safety risks and costly repairs.
symptoms: The A/C condenser is falling through
and the body mounts are being compromised.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or entering fail-safe mode can cause loss of power and control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or enters fail-safe mode
often accompanied by warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Spark plug issues can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Spark plugs are difficult to remove
break
or cause damage to the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Wiring harness failure can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to potential safety risks and costly repairs.
symptoms: The wiring harness within the engine melts against the exhaust manifold.

symptoms: The engine stalls
the vehicle loses power
the "Engine Fail Safe Mode" warning indicator illuminates

the vehicle loses power

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power and stalling of the engine while driving can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies while driving

and the power steering and brakes may become unresponsive.
